when he started following me.

352
00:24:28,330 --> 00:24:30,530
He couldn't fathom the
intricacies of military affiliations.

353
00:24:32,660 --> 00:24:35,180
All he remembered was his
brother enlisting in the army.

354
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:36,330
That's why he

355
00:24:36,740 --> 00:24:38,260
traveled with me
across various military camps.

356
00:24:43,610 --> 00:24:44,500
I see.

357
00:24:45,570 --> 00:24:46,130
[Buqu.]

358
00:24:47,050 --> 00:24:47,570
[Buqu,]

359
00:24:49,460 --> 00:24:51,090
the enemy
is challenging us to battle again.

360
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:52,330
Not again.

361
00:24:52,330 --> 00:24:54,220
They even bought cavalries this time.

362
00:24:54,850 --> 00:24:55,900
They might charge our camp.

363
00:24:58,260 --> 00:24:59,180
Get my battle armor ready.

364
00:24:59,810 --> 00:25:00,420
Wait.

365
00:25:00,850 --> 00:25:02,180
You can't join the fight today.

366
00:25:02,180 --> 00:25:03,900
Aggravating the wound
could impede its healing.

367
00:25:04,130 --> 00:25:05,220
Mr. Liu, we can't afford to wait.

368
00:25:05,220 --> 00:25:05,770
Pingwei,

369
00:25:05,900 --> 00:25:07,050
gather a hundred archers

370
00:25:07,050 --> 00:25:07,900
to confront the enemy.

371
00:25:07,900 --> 00:25:08,850
I'll monitor their movements.

372
00:25:09,090 --> 00:25:09,610
Yes.

373
00:25:10,180 --> 00:25:10,740
General.

374
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:13,090
Du Bin and I will go with you

375
00:25:13,090 --> 00:25:13,940
to be on the safe side.

376
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:24,980
[Jincheng Town]

377
00:25:34,570 --> 00:25:35,180
General,

378
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:37,260
the enemy has been challenging us
for two days.

379
00:25:37,260 --> 00:25:39,290
They have cavalry in the front
and infantry in the rear.

380
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:41,180
It seems they're planning a camp assault.

381
00:26:09,660 --> 00:26:11,130
They're emphasizing their cavalry
this time,

382
00:26:11,700 --> 00:26:13,570
trying to exploit our weaknesses.

383
00:26:14,090 --> 00:26:15,460
Our archers and long spearmen

384
00:26:15,460 --> 00:26:16,660
are ready for action.

385
00:26:17,020 --> 00:26:18,260
It's unlikely the enemy
will attempt a direct attack.

386
00:26:19,290 --> 00:26:21,370
We should split into units,

387
00:26:21,570 --> 00:26:24,020
maneuver around, engage the enemy,

388
00:26:24,020 --> 00:26:24,940
or feign defeat

389
00:26:24,940 --> 00:26:26,770
to lure them into our trap.

390
00:26:26,770 --> 00:26:28,460
What if they attempt a direct attack?

391
00:26:29,180 --> 00:26:29,740
Well...

392
00:26:30,810 --> 00:26:31,940
We'll have to face them head-on then.

393
00:26:33,090 --> 00:26:34,810
-He's right.
-What if it's a direct attack?

394
00:26:34,810 --> 00:26:35,370
Yeah.

395
00:26:46,090 --> 00:26:46,810
Anything else?

396
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:52,900
General,

397
00:26:53,980 --> 00:26:55,900
although I've never fought in battles,

398
00:26:55,900 --> 00:26:57,330
I've studied some military literature

399
00:26:57,660 --> 00:26:59,180
and have a strategy to propose.

400
00:26:59,370 --> 00:27:00,130
Would you be open to hearing it?

401
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:01,770
Of course. Please go ahead.

402
00:27:03,770 --> 00:27:05,940
While Master and I were
working in the military camp,

403
00:27:06,260 --> 00:27:08,700
we noticed that the enemy forces
had been persistently disrupted by our army

404
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:10,460
and were low on supplies
due to distance from support.

405
00:27:10,460 --> 00:27:11,610
Their troops and horses

406
00:27:11,700 --> 00:27:12,850
appear exhausted and fatigued.

407
00:27:13,660 --> 00:27:15,130
While I was on the lookout from the tower,

408
00:27:15,370 --> 00:27:17,130
I noticed the same indicators.

409
00:27:17,420 --> 00:27:18,220
What supports your claim?

410
00:27:19,810 --> 00:27:20,460
Lately,

411
00:27:20,740 --> 00:27:22,460
I've been observing from the tower

412
00:27:22,460 --> 00:27:23,420
while the enemies are cooking.

413
00:27:23,810 --> 00:27:25,770
I noticed that they use large iron pots

414
00:27:25,900 --> 00:27:27,330
for cooking in their camp.

415
00:27:27,660 --> 00:27:29,460
Using our own camp as a reference,

416
00:27:29,940 --> 00:27:32,180
I deduced
that approximately thirty soldiers

417
00:27:32,180 --> 00:27:33,900
share a single pot and stove.

418
00:27:34,370 --> 00:27:36,810
This plan simplifies mobility and combat.

419
00:27:37,220 --> 00:27:38,660
They arrange themselves in thirties.

420
00:27:38,660 --> 00:27:39,330
I guess

421
00:27:39,900 --> 00:27:41,220
the enemy has a similar approach.

422
00:27:42,370 --> 00:27:43,460
Moreover, I realized

423
00:27:43,770 --> 00:27:44,330
that recently,

424
00:27:44,770 --> 00:27:46,050
the enemy's cooking frequency

425
00:27:46,050 --> 00:27:47,090
has visibly decreased.

426
00:27:48,810 --> 00:27:49,660
How do you know that?

427
00:27:49,900 --> 00:27:50,740
Jincheng Town is dry.

428
00:27:50,740 --> 00:27:51,940
To start a fire,

429
00:27:51,940 --> 00:27:53,810
a specific type of dry twig is needed.

430
00:27:54,180 --> 00:27:56,330
While these twigs burn easily,

431
00:27:56,420 --> 00:27:57,770
they also produce dense smoke.

432
00:27:58,420 --> 00:27:59,940
Lately, I noticed

433
00:27:59,940 --> 00:28:01,850
a significant reduction
in the enemy's smoke.

434
00:28:02,330 --> 00:28:03,660
In such circumstances,

435
00:28:03,660 --> 00:28:04,660
there's only one likely explanation.

436
00:28:05,050 --> 00:28:06,020
They're running low on food.

437
00:28:06,530 --> 00:28:07,850
Looks like you've figured it out too.

438
00:28:14,290 --> 00:28:15,330
You are meticulous

439
00:28:16,180 --> 00:28:17,130
and keen.

440
00:28:18,180 --> 00:28:18,940
Well done.

441
00:28:21,180 --> 00:28:23,180
Given this military situation,

442
00:28:23,570 --> 00:28:24,610
do you have any strategies in mind?

443
00:28:25,380 --> 00:28:26,020
Well,

444
00:28:26,260 --> 00:28:28,020
considering the enemy's soldiers
are starving,

445
00:28:28,370 --> 00:28:29,300
their horses

446
00:28:29,300 --> 00:28:30,570
must be starving too.

447
00:28:31,170 --> 00:28:32,170
In that case,

448
00:28:32,500 --> 00:28:33,300
why not

449
00:28:33,300 --> 00:28:34,890
distribute some freshly cooked black beans

450
00:28:34,890 --> 00:28:36,610
to our front-line soldiers

451
00:28:36,980 --> 00:28:38,740
and scatter them on the ground

452
00:28:38,980 --> 00:28:40,740
when the enemy cavalry approaches?

453
00:28:42,260 --> 00:28:43,650
Wait, Du Bin.

454
00:28:44,330 --> 00:28:46,090
The enemy is about to attack our city,

455
00:28:46,220 --> 00:28:47,540
and you want to feed them?

456
00:28:47,540 --> 00:28:48,810
That doesn't seem like a wise plan.

457
00:28:55,370 --> 00:28:56,300
Continue.

458
00:28:58,090 --> 00:28:58,740
The aroma

459
00:28:59,300 --> 00:29:00,780
of black beans will waft through the air,

460
00:29:01,570 --> 00:29:03,370
and once the starving horses

461
00:29:04,370 --> 00:29:06,020
catch the scent of black beans,

462
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:07,890
they're likely to scatter
in all directions

463
00:29:07,890 --> 00:29:09,610
and disregard the enemy's commands.

464
00:29:11,090 --> 00:29:12,700
We can use this chance

465
00:29:12,980 --> 00:29:14,540
to launch a surprise attack.

466
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:20,850
Take my orders.

467
00:29:21,300 --> 00:29:21,890
Yes.

468
00:29:22,460 --> 00:29:23,410
Do as Du Bin said.

469
00:29:23,940 --> 00:29:24,700
Get ready now.

470
00:29:24,850 --> 00:29:25,460
Roger.

471
00:29:38,980 --> 00:29:41,180
[Jincheng Town]

472
00:31:59,610 --> 00:32:00,170
Retreat.

473
00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:00,890
Let's go.

474
00:32:00,980 --> 00:32:02,300
-Quick.
-Hurry up.

475
00:32:29,540 --> 00:32:30,220
Master,

476
00:32:32,980 --> 00:32:34,570
